metadata.name: Versus in Motion #114
metadata.description:
"Versus in Motion" is an animated version, a successor of original "Versus" collection
https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/21865

Includes all features of "Versus" (resolution levels, switchable orientation, etc) plus it's animated (obviously) and interactive
- You can stop & start animation at any time by pressing the spacebar
- You may click (or click & drag) while in animation or not, to modify the current artwork

Animation cycle is actually a transition between a "full" and an "empty" state that symbolizes the transition between existence, non-existence,  prosperity & decline and the evolution and progress in general as a result of time passage..

All are pure code, shapes and curves that processed in a custom fragment glsl (webgl) shader using a relative "advanced" developed mixing technique.

CONTROLS

KEYS:

- 1-4: Set resolution from 1x to 4x of the current dimension (possibly slower performance in higher values)
- S: Save a png file with the current resolution

- P: Change orientation to Portrait with aspect ratio 0.75 (useful eg. for printing)
- L: Change orientation to Landscape with ratio 4/3  (1.333..)
- O: Original orientation. That is the default Square (box)
  Due to some 1:1 ratio sensitive calculations, rendering output may differ when switching 
  orientations

  For animation:
- Spacebar: toggle animation (on/off)
- R: Reset the center of animation (if has been modified with click or drag)

MOUSE:

- Click (or Click & Drag) to set the center of animation

----
Made with p5js and custom shaders

© Dec. 2022  @Uniray_net | uniray.net

metadata.name: Gkrint #127
metadata.description:
Gkrint is a celebration of minimalism, colour, and space using the humble grid, a foundation of generative art, and movement. Through this collaboration, Ballzerino and George explore the relationships between these elements.

Inspired by the timeless principles of Bauhaus design, Ballzerino carefully curated custom colour palettes and selected geometric shapes, while George encoded the creative process into an algorithm, bringing the compositions to life, and putting the CPU to work finding new and unexpected compositions within our framework.

Gkrint is Ballzerino's genesis generative art drop.

Controls:
SPACE - pause / resume
click (or tap) - change colour selection (within same palette)
hold 'f' - speed up animation

Tested on Windows / Mac / iOS / Android. Chrome recommended for the best experience.

metadata.name: Glossolalia #185
metadata.description:
This series is ultimately about catharsis. The compositions can be chaotic and maybe even a little messy, but they also can be vibrant and diverse… which is really what this is trying to celebrate: diversity and expression.

Simply, it’s about the emotions associated with whatever frees you.

Please see the linked fxtext article (on the main project page) for a more in-depth dissection of the concept. It’s less of a technical discussion, and more about the experience of the artist, and how it became linked with the feelings they associate with the art.

In live mode:

For higher resolutions, you can append “&density=2” to the url to double the size, “&density=3” to triple, and so on.
(This is highly recommended.)

To adjust grain, you can append “&grain=##” to the url. 40 is the default, and 0 will remove it completely.

metadata.name: Fractal Painting #256
metadata.description:
This is composition art based on mathematics fractal.

Color Pallet has 10 variations.
Frame Line has 2 variations.

Controls (in live view):
- Press [f] to switch full screen on and off
- Press [s] to download a PNG file with windowsize
- Press [l] to download a PNG file with large size 4800 pixel (wait a minutes)

Create with p5.js

metadata.name: Foundations #156
metadata.description:
In march of this year, I started working on a new series involving multi-layering, and overriding shapes. Drawing and playing with colors and opacity.
It started with squares and grid, it then involved deformations, and circles and other experimentations.
This path fits with my artistic generative approach: rather than having a completely predefined idea, I start with a simple concept that evolves during creation. Then surprises happened, and I embraced them.

But this year was not like any other: 2022 has gifted me with a new birthday, the one of my son.

Over the past twelve months, I’ve watched him discovering the world surrounding him, learning and trying new things, laughing, or getting frustrated, sad or happy…
While learning to become a parent, I’ve been in an introspection phase where I questioned what it means to be “a father”. What impact will I have on my son, consciously or not?

“Foundations” takes shape in this context: 2 humans trying and exploring while being inspired by each other.
This series is a first of a set of at least 3, that illustrates an idea of what is an “Identity”, and what makes us who we are.

The foundations of an identity are laid in the first days of a child’s life. They will be influenced by many factors; including parenting, cultural environment, life experiences… 
Of course, as humans we are in constant evolution; life happens, sometimes for the best, sometimes for the worst, and our personality will be impacted…
But this will be a topic for another time. 


Today, we are at the start.

metadata.name: Faux #291
metadata.description:
This project is borne out of my longstanding fascination with brushwork, and the intricate textures that can be created with a brush, some paint and a canvas. Brush strokes are simulated using many overlapping lines and given texture and depth using a custom shader. Another important aspect of this work, is the composite forms that are created by the brush strokes, which are my attempt to emulate the emphatic energy of many abstract painters that have come before me. Color palettes are named after common paint colors, based on the background color used for the palette.

Those who collect during the first tier of the Dutch Auction can claim a signed print. They will be printed on A3 Hahnemuhle Photo Rag, and shipped to the collector free of charge. More details on how to claim a print and specify the necessary shipping information will be provided via the artists twitter (@landlinesart1).

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels.

metadata.name: f-emerald #224
metadata.description:
f-emerald generates unique ephemeral crystal-like structures that morph in space. each generation has a different shape, animation and colour palette. 

the crystals flicker with colours in the dark most of the time. there is, however, a 20% chance of obtaining a crystal on a bright background with a light colour palette and one out of ten structures is created in black and white.
